{"version":2,"title":"The Lord of the Rings","author":"J.R.R. Tolkien","state":{"lastAnalyzedIndex":71,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["B.B.","Old Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The elderly hobbit who discovered the One Ring and lived in the Shire for a long time.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Bilbo gives Frodo his mithril-coat and Sting, asks Frodo to help tidy and organize his notes and papers, and mentions thinking about joining Gandalf in the woods of the Shire."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin","Gandalf the Gray"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Unknown (arrived but not left)","description":"A wizard and leader of the Fellowship, played a significant role in the quest to destroy the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Departed for the West aboard the ship."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Not specified (departed on a ship)","description":"The sole Ring-bearer, who carried the One Ring and completed its destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Uncle"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Friend and former servant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Departed to the Grey Havens and sailed into the West across the Sea."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Merry","Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Buckland","description":"A hobbit friend of Frodo and Sam, a member of the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Buckland with Merry."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Fellow hobbit and servant of Frodo Baggins, who accompanied Frodo on his journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Former master and friend"},{"character":"Rose Cotton","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Stayed behind with Merry and Pippin at the Grey Havens while Frodo, Bilbo, and Gandalf departed."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion","King Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir to the throne of Gondor, who finally claims his place as king and marries Arwen Undómiel.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"wife"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn plants a sapling of the white tree that blooms before the summer solstice and weds Arwen Undómiel."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butterbur"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"An innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, a popular establishment in Bree.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the current state of the Shire and the travelers' changes since their journey."},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],