Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The daughter of Elrond and mortal woman, Elwing.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"husband"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Marries King Elessar in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Celeborn","aliases":["Lord of Lothlórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Unknown (departed to the West)","description":"A noble elf lord of Lothlórien, husband to Galadriel.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Departed for the West aboard the ship."},{"name":"Rose Cotton","aliases":["Rose Gardner"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"The wife of Samwise Gamgee, Rose was a resident of the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Wife"},{"character":"Elanor Gamgee","relationship":"Daughter"}],"recentEvents":"Received Samwise back at Bywater."},{"name":"Elanor Gamgee","aliases":["Lanor"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"The young daughter of Samwise and Rose Gamgee.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Rose Gamgee","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received Samwise back at Bywater."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo's home in the Shire, a cozy and comfortable hobbit hole that has now become a site of confrontation with Saruman."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"An area of hills and burial mounds to the south of Bree, where ancient kings were entombed."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village at the crossroads where various travelers meet. It features The Prancing Pony inn, which is the center of local social life."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The City of the Kings in Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."},{"name":"Hobbiton","description":"The home of hobbits in the Shire, where Frodo and Bilbo live."},{"name":"Shire","description":"The land where hobbits live, known for its peace, agricultural productivity, and relative isolation."},{"name":"Brandywine Bridge","description":"A bridge crossing the Brandywine River, marking the entrance to the land of Buckland and the Shire proper."},{"name":"The Grey Havens","description":"The port city where the Elves depart for their ultimate destination beyond the sea."},{"name":"Mithlond","description":"An alternative name for the Grey Havens, the port city where the elves prepare to depart."}],"summary":"Frodo, Bilbo, Gandalf, and other elves leave Middle-earth to sail into the West across the Sea, while Sam, Merry, and Pippin remain in the Shire to continue their lives there."},"snapshots":[{"index":6,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bag End","description":"The eccentric, adventurous hobbit who returns from a great journey 60 years prior to the story's present, known for his mysterious ring and his upcoming birthday celebration.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"nephew"},{"character":"Thain Peregrin","relationship":"relative"}],"recentEvents":"Planned a party for the 111th birthday celebration, which Gandalf suspected might have to do with the mysterious ring."},{"name":"Gandalf","aliases":["the Grey Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bag End","des