ding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents 