ndir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"A region of hills along the Anduin River, known for the Argonath and the daunting passage through them."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"One of the three hills surrounding Nen Hithoel, formerly used for watch posts."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"One of the three hills surrounding Nen Hithoel, formerly used for watch posts."}],"summary":"The Fellowship of the Ring continues its journey down the Anduin River, passing through the dark chasm of the Argonath and emerging into the wide waters of Nen Hithoel. The group faces awe and fear as they navigate the towering statues of Isildur and Anárion, and now finds itself at a critical junction in their quest, with the last stage of their journey before them."}},{"index":29,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An ancient and powerful wizard, also known as Mithrandir to the Elves.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion"}],"recentEvents":"Fought a Balrog and fell in