e":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A range of mountains that form a barrier between the lands to the west and the lands to the east."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"A range of rough hills and cliffs to the east of Lothlórien."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"One of the three hills surrounding Nen Hithoel, formerly used for watch posts."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."}],"summary":"Frodo and Sam have parted ways with the rest of the Fellowship to travel to Mordor on their own. Aragorn has gone in search of them."}},{"index":31,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"re