o the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captain of Gondor, member of the Fellowship of the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Fellow traveler and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Left the others after the boats incident to follow the two hobbits."},{"name":"Legolas","aliases":["Prince of Mirkwood"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Fangorn Forest","description":"An Elf from the Woodland Realm who became part of the Fellowship of the Ring","relationships":[{"character":"Thranduil","relationship":"father"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas, with Aragorn and Gimli, set out on foot after their horses disappeared in Fangorn Forest. They encounter the forest's eerie qualities and the disappearance of their horses."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A Dwarf who became part of the Fellowship of the Ring","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Thorin Oakenshield","relationship":"ancestor"}],"recentEvents":"Gimli, with Aragorn and Legolas, set out on foot after the horses they had borrowed from Rohan were taken or scared away by a mysterious old man, possibly Saruman. The companions are now wary and cautious in the mysterious forest of Fangorn."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["Sauron's Man of Knowledge"],"importance":"primary antagonist","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fellowship of the Ring","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A former Maia who was corrupted by Sauron and turned to evil","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"rival/enemy"},{"character":"Isengard","relationship":"ruler"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman possibly appeared as an old man in Fangorn Forest, scaring away the horses the companions were using."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"A range of rough hills and cliffs to the east of Lothlórien."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."}],"summary":"Merry and Pippin escape the Uruk-hai raiders, aided by an unknown Fangorn Forest, and watch as the Riders of Rohan charge to destroy the raiding party. Uglúk, the Orc captain, meets his demise at the edge of the forest, ending in a celebration of the fallen by the Riders."}},{"index":34,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An ancient and powerful wizard, also known as Mithrandir to the Elves.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion"}],"recentEvents":"Fought a Balrog and fell into a chasm."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["The Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The Hobbit who carries the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Former protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Flees across the river and heads to Mordor alone."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Mister Brandybuck"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, part of Frodo's Fellowship, known for his knowledge of the lands east of the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend and cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Helped Pippin escape the orc raiders by the Entwash and fled into the Fangorn Forest"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The loyal gardener and servant of Frodo Baggins.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Servant and companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Former protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Follows Frodo across the river."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"Merry and Pippin, having joined the Ents led by Treebeard.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Hostile towards"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the Ents on their march to Isengard and saw the forest awaken and march."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A ranger who is secretly the heir to the throne of Gondor and Isildur's heir","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"friend and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn, with Legolas and Gimli, set out on foot after the horses of Rohan they had ridden were taken or scared away by a mysterious old man, p