."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."}],"summary":"Théoden King prepares to lead the last host of Rohan westward, leaving the people in the care of his sister-daughter Éowyn. Éomer reconciles with Gimli and the group sets off with Gandalf and his newfound horse, Shadowfax."}},{"index":37,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocati