e, part of Frodo's Fellowship, known for his knowledge of the lands east of the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend and cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Helped Pippin escape the orc raiders by the Entwash and fled into the Fangorn Forest"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The loyal gardener and servant of Frodo Baggins.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Servant and companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Former protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Follows Frodo across the river."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"Merry and Pippin, having joined the Ents led by Treebeard.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Hostile towards"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the Ents on their march to Isengard and saw the forest awaken and march."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire 