"name":"Saruman","aliases":["Saruman of Many Colours","Curunir"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A deposed wizard allied with Sauron, now seen as a traitor for his acts against the forest and trees of Isengard.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Foes"},{"character":"Theoden","relationship":"Hostile towards"}],"recentEvents":"His actions against the forest have angered the Ents, who are now marching on his stronghold at Isengard."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Ent"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A wise and ancient Ent whose primary concern is the wellbeing of the forest and trees.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Led a march of Ents to attack Isengard in response to Saruman's destruction of the forest."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fighting with Elrond's aid","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"King of Rohan, a stern and wise ruler who has recently reclaimed his true self and is leading his people to victory.","relationships":[{"character":"Eomer","relationship":"nephew and trusted advisor"},{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"recent ally"},{"character":"Eowyn","relationship":"niece"}],"recentEvents":"Led a charge from Helm's Gate, driving back the Orcs and enemies of Isengard."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"A range of rough hills and cliffs to the east of Lothlórien."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entr