lationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A captain of Gondor, member of the Fellowship of the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Fellow traveler and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Left the others after the boats incident to follow the two hobbits."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf from Mirkwood, skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Rested from the recent battle with Merry."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["Saruman of Many Colours","Curunir"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A deposed wizard allied with Sauron, now seen as a traitor for his acts against the forest and trees of Isengard.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Foes"},{"character":"Theoden","relationship":"Hostile towards"}],"recentEvents":"His actions against the forest have angered the Ents, who are now marching on his stronghold at Isengard."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A wise Ent who acts as the leader of his race.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Helped and instructed"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Helped and instructed"}],"recentEvents":"Destroyed Isen, dealt with Wormtongue, and prepared food for the arriving group."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"A range of rough hills and cliffs to the east of Lothlórien."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Wizard, now under the control of Ents and nature."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."}],"summary":"Gandalf的任务是摧毁Isen，Ents已经完成了这个任务。Pippin和Merry在Isen遇到了Treebeard，并且得到了他提供的食物。Wormtongue被Treebeard骗进了Orthanc。Aragorn正在为即将到来的罗翰盟友做准备。"}},{"index":40,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A powerful wizard and guide for the main characters.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Travel partner"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Has sent Ents to destroy Isen and is believed to be on his way back there."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["The Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The Hobbit who carries the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Former protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Flees across the river and heads to Mordor alone."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The loyal gardener and servant of Frodo Baggins.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Servant and companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Former protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Follows Frodo across the river."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Voice of Saruman","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A young Hobbit from the Shire, part of the Fellowship and a significant member of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Assisted with finding food and discovered pipe-weed barrels belonging to Hornblower."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discusse