th a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Gaffer's son"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Cave in Ithilien (Osgiliath area)","description":"Frodo's loyal gardener and best friend, a brave and shrewd hobbit.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"master and close friend"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"protector"}],"recentEvents":"Sam confesses Boromir's true desires and their own quest to Faramir without hesitation.\nSam acknowledges the quality of Faramir and refers to him as Gandalf-like."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","