"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Cave in Ithilien (Osgiliath area)","description":"The younger brother of Denethor and the Captain of Gondor, wise and fair to strangers.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"protector and ally"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"protector"}],"recentEvents":"Faramir shows great wisdom and restraint when told about the Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Gollum","aliases":["Sméagol"],"importance":"major","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An obsessive creature that once possessed the One Ring and now serves Frodo as a guide.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Captured servant"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Enemy and captive"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum's whereabouts is unclear, but Sam speculates about his survival in the Oliphaunt encounter and battle."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and dangerous region controlled by Sauron where the Ring must be destroyed"},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"A verdant and rolling region south-east of Gondor, now populated with hidden Gondor soldiers"},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."}],"summary":"Frodo and Sam, having reached a hidden cave in Ithilien, encounter the wise Captain Faramir. After some trepidation, Frodo reveals their mission to destroy the Ring and Sam confesses the true nature of the Ring's influence on Boromir. Faramir understands the gravity of their mission and offers them rest and safety."}},{"index":47,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard who serves as a mentor and guide to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guide and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin ride from Isengard to Helm's Deep, then towards Minas Tirith. Gandalf explains the perilous situation to Pippin."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo son of Drogo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A Hobbit from the Shire tasked with destroying the One Ring to prevent dominion by Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Guide (of questionable reliability)"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Close friend and follower"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former mentor and guide"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Friendly and supportive ally"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo and his guide Gollum meet Faramir, who warns them against approaching Minas Morgul and Cirith Ungol due to dark terrors in the Mountains of Shadow."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Gaffer's son"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Cave in Ithilien (Osgiliath area)","description":"Frodo's loyal gardener and best friend, a brave and shrewd hobbit.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"master and close friend"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"protector"}],"recentEvents":"Sam confesses Boromir's true desires and their own quest to Faramir without hesitation.\nSam acknowledges the quality of Faramir and refers to him as Gandalf-like."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit and member of the Fellowship, known for his curiosity and bravery.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Protégé"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin has inadvertently used the Palantír at Isengard, leading Gandalf to lecture him about star stones and their danger."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Gollum","aliases":["Sméagol"],"importance":"major","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An obsessive creature that once possessed the One Ring and now serves Frodo as a guide.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Captured servant"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Enemy and captive"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum's whereabouts is unclear, but Sam speculates about his survival in the Oliphaunt encounter and battle."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and dangerous region controlled by Sauron where the Ring must be destroyed"},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."}],"summary":"Frodo and Gollum are warned by Faramir, a Gondorian warrior, against approaching Minas Morgul and the pass of Cirith Ungol. Faramir implores Frodo to rethink his path, but Frodo is bound by his promise to reach the mountains. Gollum guides them through the dangerous area of Ithilien."}},{"index":48,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard who serves as a mentor and guide to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guide and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin ride from Isengard to Helm's Deep, then towards Minas Tirith. Gandalf explains the perilous situation to Pippin."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 12","currentLocation":"Cross-roads","description":"A hobbit who carries the One Ring on a perilous journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Fellow traveller and loyal companion"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Captured creature that guides them"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo guides Sam to the Cross-roads and finds ancient symbols on the statue near the road."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 12","currentLocation":"Cross-roads","description":"A loyal hobbit follower and friend to Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Travelling companion and friend"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Travelling guide and suspect"}],"recentEvents":"Sam is wary of Gollum's urgency and helps Frodo observe the ancient statue."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit and member of the Fellowship, known for his curiosity and bravery.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Protégé"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin has inadvertently used the Palantír at Isengard, leading Gandalf to lecture him about star stones and their danger."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Gollum","aliases":["Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 12","currentLocation":"Cross-roads","description":"A scheming and tormented creature who once possessed the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Captured and occasionally helpful guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Distrusted companion"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum leads Frodo and Sam to the Cross-roads and hurries them to continue the journey."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and dangerous region controlled by Sauron where the Ring must be destroyed"},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."}],"summary":"Frodo, Sam, and Gollum reach the Cross-roads, a strategic junction under ancient trees, and witness ominous signs along the road. Gollum hurriedly guides them towards the southern path, growing increasingly wary of the tension and urgency."}},{"index":49,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard who serves as a mentor and guide to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guide and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin ride from Isengard to Helm's Deep, then towards Minas Tirith. Gandalf explains the perilous situation to Pippin."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master","Baggins"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passage","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Leader of the Fellowship; bears the One Ring and is tasked with destroying it.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and close friend"},{"character":"Sméagol","relationship":"Guide"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam sleep while Gollum searches ahead. Upon waking, Frodo confronts Gollum about continuing their journey."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Gaffer's son"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passage","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Frodo’s loyal servant, friend, and protector; accompanies him throughout his quest.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close friend"},{"character":"Sméagol","relationship":"Guide"}],"recentEvents":"Sam watches over Frodo as he sleeps and confronts Gollum upon waking."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit and member of the Fellowship, known for his curiosity and bravery.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Protégé"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin has inadvertently used the Palantír at Isengard, leading Gandalf to lecture him about star stones and their danger."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passage","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Deceitful but sometimes helpful guide given to Frodo by the Wizard Gandalf; conflicted about his desire to possess the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guide"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum guides the sleepers, expresses conflicted feelings when near rest and food."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and dangerous region controlled by Sauron where the Ring must be destroyed"},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."}],"summary":"In the passage before the final confrontation, Frodo and Sam rest while Gollum scours ahead for the path. Frodo and Sam discuss with Gollum the possibility of continuing the journey alone, but Gollum insists on accompanying them through the final leg, as he claims they cannot find the path by themselves."}},{"index":50,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard who serves as a mentor and guide to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guide and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin ride from Isengard to Helm's Deep, then towards Minas Tirith. Gandalf explains the perilous situation to Pippin."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Mr. Frodo","Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Hobbit from the Shire, given the task of destroying the One Ring by the wizard Gandalf.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Friend and follower"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo was treacherously abandoned by Gollum who intended to hand him over to Shelob, a monstrous spider. Frodo was unaware of Gollum's betrayal and ran into deadly danger."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Samwise"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Sam is a loyal Hobbit gardener and friend to Frodo. He protects and assists Frodo on his quest.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Companion and de facto leader"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Samwise was left behind by Gollum in his treacherous attempt to capture Frodo. He discovered Gollum's betrayal and fought back to save Frodo, but Gollum escaped. Sam pursued Gollum but failed to overtake him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit and member of the Fellowship, known for his curiosity and bravery.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Protégé"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin has inadvertently used the Palantír at Isengard, leading Gandalf to lecture him about star stones and their danger."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":null,"currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A giant spider-like creature with a lair along Frodo's path in Mordor.","relationships":[{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Partnered to capture prey"}],"recentEvents":"Shelob emerged to attack Frodo after Gollum left him. She nearly captured Frodo."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."}],"summary":"Samwise Gamgee and Frodo Baggins continue their journey through Mordor. Gollum betrays them, intending to capture Frodo for Shelob, a monstrous spider. Sam intervenes and fights Gollum but Gollum escapes, leaving Frodo to the dire peril of Shelob."}},{"index":51,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard who serves as a mentor and guide to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guide and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin ride from Isengard to Helm's Deep, then towards Minas Tirith. Gandalf explains the perilous situation to Pippin."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit and member of the Fellowship, known for his curiosity and bravery.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Protégé"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin has inadvertently used the Palantír at Isengard, leading Gandalf to lecture him about star stones and their danger."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."}],"summary":"Sam discovers Frodo is alive but imprisoned in Barad-dûr after being captured by the Orcs Shagrat and Gorbag. Sam attempts to rescue Frodo but fails and is left senseless outside the gate."}},{"index":52,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard who serves as a mentor and guide to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guide and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin ride from Isengard to Helm's Deep, then towards Minas Tirith. Gandalf explains the perilous situation to Pippin."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Road to Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit and member of the Fellowship, known for his curiosity and bravery.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Protégé"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin has inadvertently used the Palantír at Isengard, leading Gandalf to lecture him about star stones and their danger."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The ancient capital and largest city of Gondor, a city built upon seven levels on the side of a great hill."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."}],"summary":"Sam discovers Frodo is alive but imprisoned in Barad-dûr after being captured by the Orcs Shagrat and Gorbag. Sam attempts to rescue Frodo but fails and is left senseless outside the gate."}},{"index":53,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard and main ally of the protagonists against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Confidant and advisor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Minas Tirith to speak with Denethor and prepare to take Pippin to see him early the next morning."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Road to Isengard","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit of the Shire, loyal companion of Merry and warrior of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Best friend and fellow companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Respected captain of Gondor"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Saw troops arrive from the Outlands to defend Minas Tirith, was guided around the city by Beregond’s son Bergil, and met Gandalf late at night."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Treebeard","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A descendant of Isildur and a key figure in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Prepared for the arrival of allies from Rohan and discussed the situation with Pippin."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"An Elf warrior from Mirkwood, son of Glóin.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Legolas introduced Gimli to Treebeard and made a deal to visit Fangorn's Wood."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Gimli son of Glóin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"A Dwarf, skilled warrior and craftsman.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Reunited with Merry and Pippin after a long journey, expressed anger and joy at their situation."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":["Third Company Commander"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A captain of the guard and member of the Third Company, Beregond is a father who cares for his son and respects Gandalf.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Welcomes and cares for the hobbit"},{"character":"Bergil","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Met with Pippin and gave him news that he will be summoned by Lord Denethor."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a kinsman of Denethor and brings men of the South to aid in the defense of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Kinsman"}],"recentEvents":"Led a company of knights and men to Minas Tirith to aid in its defense."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The White City and capital of Gondor, a place under siege and facing darkness."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."}],"summary":"Pippin spends time in Minas Tirith, guided by Beregond's son Bergil, and observes forces from the Outlands arriving to defend the city. In the evening, he meets Gandalf who has ominous news about the start of darkness."}},{"index":54,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard and main ally of the protagonists against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Confidant and advisor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Minas Tirith to speak with Denethor and prepare to take Pippin to see him early the next morning."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merri"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Isen","description":"A Hobbit and friend of Pippin's, part of the quest against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Mentor and protector"}],"recentEvents":"Helped find food and watched for incoming allies from the Rohirric forces."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Road to Isengard","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit of the Shire, loyal companion of Merry and warrior of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Best friend and fellow companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Respected captain of Gondor"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Saw troops arrive from the Outlands to defend Minas Tirith, was guided around the city by Beregond’s son Bergil, and met Gandalf late at night."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Erech","description":"A human ranger who is the heir of Isildur and one of the Dúnedain.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elrohir"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elladan"}],"recentEvents":"Called upon the Oathbreakers at the Hill of Erech and led them to fulfill their oath. Led the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and into the darkness of the Storm of Mordor."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A Wood Elf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Aragorn and Gimli.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Helped guide the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and warned them of the shadowy host following them."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A dwarf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Legolas and Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Encountered the Oathbreakers and rode with the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale to Calembel."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["Théoden","Théoden King","King of the Mark","King Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Isengard","description":"King of Rohan, wise and respected leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Met and greeted Merry and Pippin, expressed curiosity about hobbits."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":["Third Company Commander"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A captain of the guard and member of the Third Company, Beregond is a father who cares for his son and respects Gandalf.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Welcomes and cares for the hobbit"},{"character":"Bergil","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Met with Pippin and gave him news that he will be summoned by Lord Denethor."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a kinsman of Denethor and brings men of the South to aid in the defense of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Kinsman"}],"recentEvents":"Led a company of knights and men to Minas Tirith to aid in its defense."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elrohir.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Unfurled the banner for Aragorn and helped lead the Company through the Morthond Vale."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elladan.","relationships":[{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Gave the black horn to Aragorn to summon the Oathbreakers and led the Company with Elladan."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A major river running through the plains east of the Shire, forming a boundary between Rohan and the former lands of Gondor."},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The White City and capital of Gondor, a place under siege and facing darkness."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The main city and seat of the King of Rohan, located in the western part of the country."},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."}],"summary":"Aragorn has called upon the Oathbreakers at the Hill of Erech and led them to fulfill their oath to follow him to Pelargir. The Grey Company, including Aragorn, Elladan, Elrohir, Legolas, and Gimli, have been traveling through the Morthond Vale and now they have arrived at Calembel, where all inhabitants have fled from fear of the approaching Dead."}},{"index":55,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard and main ally of the protagonists against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Confidant and advisor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Minas Tirith to speak with Denethor and prepare to take Pippin to see him early the next morning."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Master Meriadoc"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A hobbit friend of the Fellowship of the Ring, staunch and clever","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden King","relationship":"Swordthain"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Travels with Théoden's forces to Minas Tirith, disguised on Windfola as a burden to Dernhelm"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Road to Isengard","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit of the Shire, loyal companion of Merry and warrior of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Best friend and fellow companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Respected captain of Gondor"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Saw troops arrive from the Outlands to defend Minas Tirith, was guided around the city by Beregond’s son Bergil, and met Gandalf late at night."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Erech","description":"A human ranger who is the heir of Isildur and one of the Dúnedain.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elrohir"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elladan"}],"recentEvents":"Called upon the Oathbreakers at the Hill of Erech and led them to fulfill their oath. Led the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and into the darkness of the Storm of Mordor."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Meeting with Frodo Baggins","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A warrior of Gondor who shows kindness and wisdom towards Frodo, offering guidance and a safe conduct out of danger.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Blessed guide and friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Brother who he warned against the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo against cirith Ungol and the dark valley of Minas Morgul."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A Wood Elf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Aragorn and Gimli.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Helped guide the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and warned them of the shadowy host following them."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A dwarf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Legolas and Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Encountered the Oathbreakers and rode with the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale to Calembel."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"The aging ruler of Rohan who recently rallied from an enchantment","relationships":[{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Guard and nephew"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Aunt"}],"recentEvents":"Led the Riders of Rohan into battle towards Minas Tirith"},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":["Third Company Commander"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A captain of the guard and member of the Third Company, Beregond is a father who cares for his son and respects Gandalf.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Welcomes and cares for the hobbit"},{"character":"Bergil","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Met with Pippin and gave him news that he will be summoned by Lord Denethor."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a kinsman of Denethor and brings men of the South to aid in the defense of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Kinsman"}],"recentEvents":"Led a company of knights and men to Minas Tirith to aid in its defense."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elrohir.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Unfurled the banner for Aragorn and helped lead the Company through the Morthond Vale."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elladan.","relationships":[{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Gave the black horn to Aragorn to summon the Oathbreakers and led the Company with Elladan."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A young Rohirrim Rider who offers to take Merry along on Windfola","relationships":[{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Accompanied by"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to carry Merry into battle on Windfola"}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The White City and capital of Gondor, a place under siege and facing darkness."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"}],"summary":"King Théoden of Rohan leads his riders out of Dunharrow towards the besieged city of Minas Tirith, as a dark cloud of unease settles over the land. Despite Théoden's reluctance to allow Merry to accompany him, the hobbit travels by Dernhelm's assistance disguised as a burden on Windfola."}},{"index":56,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawnless Day","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard and key ally of the Fellowship","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade in arms"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Faced the Lord of the Nazgûl and prevented him from entering the city through the Gate."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Master Meriadoc"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A hobbit friend of the Fellowship of the Ring, staunch and clever","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden King","relationship":"Swordthain"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Travels with Théoden's forces to Minas Tirith, disguised on Windfola as a burden to Dernhelm"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Road to Isengard","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit of the Shire, loyal companion of Merry and warrior of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Best friend and fellow companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Respected captain of Gondor"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Saw troops arrive from the Outlands to defend Minas Tirith, was guided around the city by Beregond’s son Bergil, and met Gandalf late at night."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Uruk-hai captain from Isengard, tasked with capturing Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Orcs","relationship":"Leader"}],"recentEvents":"Slew by Éomer in the battle against the Rohirrim."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Erech","description":"A human ranger who is the heir of Isildur and one of the Dúnedain.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elrohir"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elladan"}],"recentEvents":"Called upon the Oathbreakers at the Hill of Erech and led them to fulfill their oath. Led the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and into the darkness of the Storm of Mordor."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Silent Street","description":"Denethor's son and valiant Captain of Gondor","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Son and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Advisor and potential rival"}],"recentEvents":"Brought to the Silent Street, his father, Denethor, plans to end his life."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A Wood Elf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Aragorn and Gimli.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Helped guide the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and warned them of the shadowy host following them."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A dwarf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Legolas and Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Encountered the Oathbreakers and rode with the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale to Calembel."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"The aging ruler of Rohan who recently rallied from an enchantment","relationships":[{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Guard and nephew"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Aunt"}],"recentEvents":"Led the Riders of Rohan into battle towards Minas Tirith"},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Captain of the Guard who is concerned for Faramir","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Asked to prevent tragedy"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Works under him"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Pippin, who has been asked to prevent Denethor's madness from causing tragedy."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a kinsman of Denethor and brings men of the South to aid in the defense of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Kinsman"}],"recentEvents":"Led a company of knights and men to Minas Tirith to aid in its defense."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elrohir.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Unfurled the banner for Aragorn and helped lead the Company through the Morthond Vale."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elladan.","relationships":[{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Gave the black horn to Aragorn to summon the Oathbreakers and led the Company with Elladan."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A young Rohirrim Rider who offers to take Merry along on Windfola","relationships":[{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Accompanied by"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to carry Merry into battle on Windfola"},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Silent Street","description":"Lord of Minas Tirith and steward of Gondor, driven to despair","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Wishes his guidance to his son"}],"recentEvents":"Carries Faramir to the Silent Street, plans to end both their lives."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city of Gondor under siege by the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."}],"summary":"Pippin tries to prevent Denethor's plans for suicide and to save Faramir. Meanwhile, in the battle outside, Gandalf and the defenders of Minas Tirith hold off the forces of Mordor, led by the Lord of the Nazgûl, until the arrival of Rohan's army."}},{"index":57,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawnless Day","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard and key ally of the Fellowship","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade in arms"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Faced the Lord of the Nazgûl and prevented him from entering the city through the Gate."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Master Meriadoc"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A hobbit friend of the Fellowship of the Ring, staunch and clever","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden King","relationship":"Swordthain"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Travels with Théoden's forces to Minas Tirith, disguised on Windfola as a burden to Dernhelm"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Road to Isengard","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit of the Shire, loyal companion of Merry and warrior of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Best friend and fellow companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Respected captain of Gondor"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Saw troops arrive from the Outlands to defend Minas Tirith, was guided around the city by Beregond’s son Bergil, and met Gandalf late at night."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Théoden’s nephew and heir, a warrior and soldier, who urges his uncle to help defend Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Uncle"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Sister"}],"recentEvents":"Led one of the éoreds in the charge towards the besieged Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Erech","description":"A human ranger who is the heir of Isildur and one of the Dúnedain.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elrohir"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Elven warrior and brother of Elladan"}],"recentEvents":"Called upon the Oathbreakers at the Hill of Erech and led them to fulfill their oath. Led the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and into the darkness of the Storm of Mordor."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Silent Street","description":"Denethor's son and valiant Captain of Gondor","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Son and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Advisor and potential rival"}],"recentEvents":"Brought to the Silent Street, his father, Denethor, plans to end his life."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A Wood Elf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Aragorn and Gimli.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Helped guide the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale and warned them of the shadowy host following them."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"A dwarf who is a part of the Grey Company and friend to Legolas and Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Encountered the Oathbreakers and rode with the Grey Company through the Morthond Vale to Calembel."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Théoden King","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"The king of Rohan, an aging leader who is motivated by his nephew Éomer and the advice of Gandalf's allies.","relationships":[{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Niece"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Adviser"}],"recentEvents":"Led his forces in a charge towards the beleaguered city of Minas Tirith and rallied his troops for battle."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Captain of the Guard who is concerned for Faramir","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Asked to prevent tragedy"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Works under him"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Pippin, who has been asked to prevent Denethor's madness from causing tragedy."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a kinsman of Denethor and brings men of the South to aid in the defense of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Kinsman"}],"recentEvents":"Led a company of knights and men to Minas Tirith to aid in its defense."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elrohir.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Unfurled the banner for Aragorn and helped lead the Company through the Morthond Vale."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Calembel","description":"An elven warrior who is part of the Grey Company and brother to Elladan.","relationships":[{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Gave the black horn to Aragorn to summon the Oathbreakers and led the Company with Elladan."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A young Rohirrim Rider who offers to take Merry along on Windfola","relationships":[{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Accompanied by"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to carry Merry into battle on Windfola"},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Silent Street","description":"Lord of Minas Tirith and steward of Gondor, driven to despair","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Wishes his guidance to his son"}],"recentEvents":"Carries Faramir to the Silent Street, plans to end both their lives."},{"name":"Éowyn","aliases":["Dernhelm, Shieldmaiden of Rohan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Theoden's Return","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Niece and sister of Éomer, disguised as a man and acting as a shieldmaiden of Rohan.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Niece"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Followed Théoden closely in the charge towards Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Banner-bearer to King Théoden of Rohan.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Banner-bearer"}],"recentEvents":"Was present with Théoden when the king led his forces into battle."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The city of Gondor under siege by the forces of Sauron, with fires burning and a great battle about to commence."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."}],"summary":"The army of Rohan, led by King Théoden, arrives at the outskirts of Minas Tirith in the midst of the night. The forces of darkness are in disarray due to the unexpected arrival. With a sudden change of weather, bringing morning and hope, Théoden leads his troops with a rallying cry to charge towards the city, turning the tide of the battle."}},{"index":58,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawnless Day","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard and key ally of the Fellowship","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade in arms"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Faced the Lord of the Nazgûl and prevented him from entering the city through the Gate."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Master Meriadoc"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A hobbit friend of the Fellowship of the Ring, staunch and clever","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden King","relationship":"Swordthain"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Travels with Théoden's forces to Minas Tirith, disguised on Windfola as a burden to Dernhelm"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Road to Isengard","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A young hobbit of the Shire, loyal companion of Merry and warrior of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Best friend and fellow companion"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Respected captain of Gondor"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Saw troops arrive from the Outlands to defend Minas Tirith, was guided around the city by Beregond’s son Bergil, and met Gandalf late at night."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Théoden’s nephew and heir, a warrior and soldier, who urges his uncle to help defend Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Uncle"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Sister"}],"recentEvents":"Led one of the éoreds in the charge towards the besieged Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Heir to the throne of Gondor, a skilled warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived at Minas Tirith with reinforcements from the Paths of the Dead, turning the tide of the battle."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Silent Street","description":"Denethor's son and valiant Captain of Gondor","relationships":[{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Son and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Advisor and potential rival"}],"recentEvents":"Brought to the Silent Street, his father, Denethor, plans to end his life."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Captain of the Guard who is concerned for Faramir","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Asked to prevent tragedy"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Works under him"}],"recentEvents":"Interacted with Pippin, who has been asked to prevent Denethor's madness from causing tragedy."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a skilled commander and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Rallied knights from Dol Amroth to fight the Easterlings."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A young Rohirrim Rider who offers to take Merry along on Windfola","relationships":[{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Accompanied by"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to carry Merry into battle on Windfola"},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Silent Street","description":"Lord of Minas Tirith and steward of Gondor, driven to despair","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Wishes his guidance to his son"}],"recentEvents":"Carries Faramir to the Silent Street, plans to end both their lives."},{"name":"Éowyn","aliases":["Dernhelm, Shieldmaiden of Rohan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Theoden's Return","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Niece and sister of Éomer, disguised as a man and acting as a shieldmaiden of Rohan.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Niece"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Followed Théoden closely in the charge towards Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The city of Gondor under siege by the forces of Sauron, with fires burning and a great battle about to commence."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."}],"summary":"The army of Rohan, led by King Théoden, arrives at the outskirts of Minas Tirith in the midst of the night. The forces of darkness are in disarray due to the unexpected arrival. With a sudden change of weather, bringing morning and hope, Théoden leads his troops with a rallying cry to charge towards the city, turning the tide of the battle."}},{"index":59,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful wizard, ally of the Free Peoples of Middle-earth and mentor to Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"student/follower"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"friend and protector"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"champion of Minas Tirith"}],"recentEvents":"Averted Faramir's suicide attempt by breaking Denethor's madness, now dealing with further challenges."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Master Meriadoc"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A hobbit friend of the Fellowship of the Ring, staunch and clever","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden King","relationship":"Swordthain"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Travels with Théoden's forces to Minas Tirith, disguised on Windfola as a burden to Dernhelm"},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Hobbit, loyal friend of Frodo, a member of the Fellowship, and now a guard of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"ally and guard"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"fellow Hobbit and friend"}],"recentEvents":"Helped carry Faramir to the Houses of Healing and accompanied Gandalf to the field."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Théoden’s nephew and heir, a warrior and soldier, who urges his uncle to help defend Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Uncle"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Sister"}],"recentEvents":"Led one of the éoreds in the charge towards the besieged Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Heir to the throne of Gondor, a skilled warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived at Minas Tirith with reinforcements from the Paths of the Dead, turning the tide of the battle."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Houses of Healing, Minas Tirith","description":"Boromir's younger brother, a Captain of Gondor, and son of Denethor.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"guard"},{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"protector"}],"recentEvents":"Saved from burning by Gandalf, Beregond, and Pippin; being tended to in the Houses of Healing."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A guard of Minas Tirith who saved Faramir from the flames of his father's folly.","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"protector"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"advisor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to the Citadel to report the events and was sent to guard Faramir in the Houses of Healing."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a skilled commander and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Rallied knights from Dol Amroth to fight the Easterlings."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Journey to Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Rohan (Folde)","description":"A young Rohirrim Rider who offers to take Merry along on Windfola","relationships":[{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Accompanied by"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to carry Merry into battle on Windfola"},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Éowyn","aliases":["Dernhelm, Shieldmaiden of Rohan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Theoden's Return","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Niece and sister of Éomer, disguised as a man and acting as a shieldmaiden of Rohan.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Niece"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Followed Théoden closely in the charge towards Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The city of Gondor under siege by the forces of Sauron, with fires burning and a great battle about to commence."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"A facility within the City of Minas Tirith for the care and treatment of sick and wounded."}],"summary":"Gandalf and Pippin manage to save Faramir from Denethor's madness and fire, leading to the revelation that Denethor had been using the Seeing Stone, allowing Sauron's influence to corrupt Minas Tirith. Denethor's death results in chaos, but hope emerges from rumors of the fall of a major captain of the enemy forces."}},{"index":60,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The wizard and powerful ally in the war against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"mentor and advisor"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"protector and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf counsels Aragorn about the treatment of Faramir and Éowyn, as well as advising the Warden of the Houses not to allow Beregond and the hobbits to discuss Denethor's madness."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Hobbit, loyal friend of Frodo, a member of the Fellowship, and now a guard of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"ally and guard"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"fellow Hobbit and friend"}],"recentEvents":"Helped carry Faramir to the Houses of Healing and accompanied Gandalf to the field."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Riders of Rohan","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"Théoden’s nephew and heir, a warrior and soldier, who urges his uncle to help defend Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Uncle"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Sister"}],"recentEvents":"Led one of the éoreds in the charge towards the besieged Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Aragorn, son of Arathorn, is the heir to the throne of Gondor and a skilled warrior.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"mentor and advisor"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"He has returned to Minas Tirith and is known as 'Elfstone' because of the green stone he wears. Aragorn has been healing those hurt or under the 'Black Shadow', and is now resting in his tent."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Boromir","aliases":["Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","none"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Denethor and steward of Gondor, who has been in recovery.","relationships":[{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Faramir, though recovering, has not yet learned of his father's death. He will soon be informed of this and other duties, according to Gandalf's instructions."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A guard of Minas Tirith who saved Faramir from the flames of his father's folly.","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"protector"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"advisor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to the Citadel to report the events and was sent to guard Faramir in the Houses of Healing."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth, a skilled commander and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Rallied knights from Dol Amroth to fight the Easterlings."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The fortified city and capital of Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"An old city now shrouded in darkness, visible on the road leading east and to the west towards the setting sun."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."}],"summary":"Aragorn has returned to Minas Tirith, named 'Elfstone' due to the green stone he wears. He is healing the wounded and resting, while Éowyn and Faramir continue to recover in the Houses of Healing. Merry begins to reflect on his service to Faramir, contemplating the broader impact of the war on those in the Shire."}},{"index":61,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"One of the Istari, a wizard and leader of the resistance against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Proposed a dangerous plan of confronting Mordor with a small force in order to lure Sauron's attention."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Master"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and the chief Ring-bearer, carrying the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"}],"recentEvents":"Captured by the Orcs, but revealed to be alive and imprisoned in a chamber in Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Hobbit, loyal friend of Frodo, a member of the Fellowship, and now a guard of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"ally and guard"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"fellow Hobbit and friend"}],"recentEvents":"Helped carry Faramir to the Houses of Healing and accompanied Gandalf to the field."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir of Isildur and future King of Gondor and Arnor","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Decided to lead seven thousand foot and a thousand horse against Mordor following Gandalf's directive."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A guard of Minas Tirith who saved Faramir from the flames of his father's folly.","relationships":[{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"protector"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"advisor"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to the Citadel to report the events and was sent to guard Faramir in the Houses of Healing."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and a distinguished Gondorian military leader","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to send three and a half thousand men as part of the expedition against Mordor."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city and fortress of Gondor, the city was heavily defended against an assault, but now sets out to challenge Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, a fortification and entry point into the dark land."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."}],"summary":"The leaders of Gondor, Rohan, and other allies held a critical planning session to determine their next course of action. With Sauron’s Eye distracted, they decided to lead a risky, small expedition to challenge Mordor directly. The strategy is to lure Sauron into a trap."}},{"index":62,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A powerful wizard who is a key leader in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Rejected the terms offered by Sauron's messenger, causing the enemies to attack the forces of the West."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo"],"importance":"main","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Journey to Mount Doom","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The Ring-bearer, a hobbit from the Shire, carrying the One Ring to destroy it.","relationships":[{"character":"Sam","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin hears that Frodo is doomed to the torment of the Tower of Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A hobbit and gardener to the chief Ring-bearer, loyal and devoted.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and close companion"}],"recentEvents":"Lost in the tunnels but hears his master is alive and imprisoned; attempts to rescue him."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal friend to the Fellowship and the leaders of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin was in the Battle of the Morannon, fought alongside Beregond and was injured by a troll but managed to kill it, though he was knocked unconscious."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir of Isildur and future King of Gondor and Arnor","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Decided to lead seven thousand foot and a thousand horse against Mordor following Gandalf's directive."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city and fortress of Gondor, the city was heavily defended against an assault, but now sets out to challenge Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A treacherous high pass and cleft in the mountains leading to the dark realm of the enemy."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."}],"summary":"The battle at Morannon begins with Sauron's forces overwhelming the outnumbered Western forces. Gandalf rejects Sauron's terms, leading to a massive assault by Mordor's army. Pippin and Beregond fight bravely but are nearly overcome, with Pippin sustaining critical injuries but managing to slay a terrifying troll."}},{"index":63,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A powerful wizard who is a key leader in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Rejected the terms offered by Sauron's messenger, causing the enemies to attack the forces of the West."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of Cirith Ungol","currentLocation":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A Hobbit and the Ring-bearer from the Shire, carrying the One Ring","relationships":[{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam escape the Tower, using the elven-glass to break the Watchers' will and escape through the gate."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of Cirith Ungol","currentLocation":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A Hobbit who is Frodo's loyal servant and friend, known for his bravery and quick thinking.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Sam uses the elven-glass to break through the gate's Watchers and lead Frodo to escape."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal friend to the Fellowship and the leaders of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin was in the Battle of the Morannon, fought alongside Beregond and was injured by a troll but managed to kill it, though he was knocked unconscious."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir of Isildur and future King of Gondor and Arnor","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Decided to lead seven thousand foot and a thousand horse against Mordor following Gandalf's directive."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city and fortress of Gondor, the city was heavily defended against an assault, but now sets out to challenge Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."}],"summary":"Frodo and Sam escape the Tower of Cirith Ungol with the help of the elven-glass, breaking the Watchers' hold and narrowly avoiding destruction from a winged shape from the sky."}},{"index":64,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A powerful wizard who is a key leader in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Rejected the terms offered by Sauron's messenger, causing the enemies to attack the forces of the West."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo, the Halfling"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Gollum Is Trapped","currentLocation":"Udûn","description":"A hobbit and the principal Ring-bearer seeking to destroy the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Protector/Companion"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo is forced to march with an orc troop to Udûn, nearly faints along the way, but manages to escape when orc troops from other directions clash and cause confusion."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam, Samson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Gollum Is Trapped","currentLocation":"Udûn","description":"A loyal hobbit gardener who accompanies Frodo on his perilous mission.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Protector/Companion"}],"recentEvents":"Sam coerces Frodo to continue marching with the orc troop, but then cleverly assists Frodo in escaping amidst a clash of several orc troops."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal friend to the Fellowship and the leaders of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin was in the Battle of the Morannon, fought alongside Beregond and was injured by a troll but managed to kill it, though he was knocked unconscious."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir of Isildur and future King of Gondor and Arnor","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Decided to lead seven thousand foot and a thousand horse against Mordor following Gandalf's directive."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Of Herbs and Stewed Rabbit","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A creature enslaved by the ring, with an internal struggle between his former self Sméagol and the corrupted personality Gollum.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Tormented him to capture him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Captured and tormented him"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum treacherously left Sam to attempt capturing Frodo, ultimately failing due to Sam's intervention."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city and fortress of Gondor, the city was heavily defended against an assault, but now sets out to challenge Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."}],"summary":"Frodo and Sam are forced to march with an orc troop to Udûn, where they narrowly escape detection and manage to fall over the edge of the road when orc troops clash, causing chaos."}},{"index":65,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A powerful wizard who is a key leader in the fight against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Rejected the terms offered by Sauron's messenger, causing the enemies to attack the forces of the West."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["The Halfling","Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Mount Doom","description":"A key member of the Fellowship, carrying the One Ring on a quest to destroy it.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Fellowship member, close friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo puts on the One Ring at the Cracks of Doom, resulting in the destruction of Sauron's power and freeing himself from the burden of the Ring."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Gaffer's son"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Mount Doom","description":"Frodo's gardener and loyal companion, who followed him to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Close friend and companion"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Respected Guide"}],"recentEvents":"Sam helps Frodo from the chasm's edge after Gollum's fatal plunge, marking the successful completion of their quest."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal friend to the Fellowship and the leaders of Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin was in the Battle of the Morannon, fought alongside Beregond and was injured by a troll but managed to kill it, though he was knocked unconscious."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir of Isildur and future King of Gondor and Arnor","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Decided to lead seven thousand foot and a thousand horse against Mordor following Gandalf's directive."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Mirkwood, a skilled archer and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Led troops from the ships to attack the enemy from behind."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city and fortress of Gondor, the city was heavily defended against an assault, but now sets out to challenge Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."}],"summary":"Frodo and Sam reach Mount Doom, where Frodo puts on the One Ring, leading to Gollum's demise and the destruction of Sauron's power. Frodo and Sam are saved from the chaos but Frodo's hand is injured."}},{"index":66,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"Former Wizard and Istari, a guide and mentor to the Fellowship of the Ring","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guardian and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Ranger ally and future king"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guide and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke of the recovery and rest of Sam and Merry."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Mr. Underhill"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"A hobbit of the Shire, the Ring-bearer, who carried the One Ring to Mordor.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Fellowship member and loyal friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion on the journey"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion on the journey"}],"recentEvents":"Slept and recovered from the brink of death with the healing of the King, along with Samwise."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit from the Shire, loyal and brave in battle.","relationships":[{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"close friend and fellow hobbit"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Merry has recovered sufficiently to request a pipe and some supper, reflecting on his service to Faramir."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Master Samwise"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"A hobbit of the Shire, guardian and friend to Frodo Baggins, the Ring-bearer","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Close friend and guardian"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion on the journey"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion on the journey"}],"recentEvents":"Slept and recovered from the brink of death with the healing of the King, along with Frodo."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Merry"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit of the Shire, member of the Fellowship of the Ring, cousin to Merry Brandybuck","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Formerly a ward under the Steward of Gondor"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion on the journey"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Former charge"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Sam and Frodo after the battle and is now a knight."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir of Isildur and future King of Gondor and Arnor","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allied with"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allied with"}],"recentEvents":"Decided to lead seven thousand foot and a thousand horse against Mordor following Gandalf's directive."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord and keeper of the Three Elven Rings of Power.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Council leader"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Presents the Council of Elrond and supports Frodo's decision to accept the burden of the One Ring."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas","Elladan","Elrohir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elf of Mirkwood, companion and friend to the Fellowship","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Companion on journey"}],"recentEvents":"Sang about his journey to the Sea."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["The Lady of Lórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful elven queen in Lothlórien, she provides counsel and magical aid to the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him a Lórien brooch"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Met in Lórien, gave him Galadriel's gift of Lórien apples"}],"recentEvents":"Sees the Fellowship off as they leave Lórien."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Elladan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elf from Imladris, a skilled warrior and tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Halbarad","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Halbarad to aid in the battle."},{"name":"Elrohir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"Capital city and fortress of Gondor, the city was heavily defended against an assault, but now sets out to challenge Mordor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."}],"summary":"Following their journey to Mordor and the defeat of Sauron, the hobbits Frodo and Sam recover in the haven of the Field of Cormallen, while Merry and Pippin return after the battle, now as knights. The field of Cormallen is near Henneth Annûn, the hidden haven in the Ithilien region where the remnants of the army of Gondor rest and prepare for the return to Minas Tirith."}},{"index":67,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Bilbo"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Inn at Bree","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Retired hobbit and the original owner of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and former heir"}],"recentEvents":"Offers to accompany Frodo but Gandalf advises against it, and he agrees."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"Former Wizard and Istari, a guide and mentor to the Fellowship of the Ring","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guardian and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Ranger ally and future king"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guide and mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke of the recovery and rest of Sam and Merry."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Mr. Underhill"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"A hobbit of the Shire, the Ring-bearer, who carried the One Ring to Mordor.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Fellowship member and loyal friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion on the journey"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion on the journey"}],"recentEvents":"Slept and recovered from the brink of death with the healing of the King, along with Samwise."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Merry","Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A hobbit of the Shire, member of the Fellowship of the Ring, cousin to Merry Brandybuck","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Cousin"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Denethor","relationship":"Formerly a ward under the Steward of Gondor"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion on the journey"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Former charge"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Sam and Frodo after the battle and is now a knight."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Master Samwise"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Henneth Annûn","description":"A hobbit of the Shire, guardian and friend to Frodo Baggins, the Ring-bearer","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Close friend and guardian"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Close friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Companion on the journey"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Companion on the journey"}],"recentEvents":"Slept and recovered from the brink of death with the healing of the King, along with Frodo."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion","King Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir to the throne of Gondor, who finally claims his place as king and marries Arwen Undómiel.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"wife"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn plants a sapling of the white tree that blooms before the summer solstice and weds Arwen Undómiel."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Master Elrond"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A powerful elf-lord in Rivendell.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"daughter"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"son-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Conveys the sceptre of Annúminas to Aragorn and consents to Arwen's marriage."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas","Elladan","Elrohir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lady of Lothlórien.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The daughter of Elrond and mortal woman, Elwing.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"husband"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Marries King Elessar in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Celeborn","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The City of the Kings in Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."}],"summary":"Aragorn marries Arwen Undómiel on Midsummer's Eve, officially becoming King Elessar of Gondor. Elrond and Galadriel, along with many other notable guests, attend the wedding in Minas Tirith. A new white tree blossoms in the city's courtyard, signifying a new era in Gondor."}},{"index":68,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["B.B.","Old Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The elderly hobbit who discovered the One Ring and lived in the Shire for a long time.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Bilbo gives Frodo his mithril-coat and Sting, asks Frodo to help tidy and organize his notes and papers, and mentions thinking about joining Gandalf in the woods of the Shire."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The wise and powerful wizard who had a great influence on the quest to destroy the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Advised ally"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Former captive"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allied commander"}],"recentEvents":"Gandalf decides to accompany the hobbits on their journey back to Bree and Butterbur."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The brave young hobbit who took on the burden of destroying the One Ring, a task he began years ago after inheriting it from his uncle Bilbo.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Uncle and guardian"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant and close friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo decides it is time to leave and returns the One Ring he was given by Bilbo, prepares to organize Bilbo’s notes and papers, and says farewell to Elrond."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Merry","Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"Frodo's young cousin and trusted friend, who accompanied him on the quest.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin receives advice and a small inheritance from Bilbo."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"Frodo's devoted gardener and friend, who accompanied him on his quest to destroy the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Master and friend"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Former employer"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and mentor"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Samwise expresses his worry about Gaffer Gamgee and his wish to stay in the Shire, agrees to help Frodo clean up and organize Bilbo’s papers, and says goodbye to the others."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion","King Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir to the throne of Gondor, who finally claims his place as king and marries Arwen Undómiel.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"wife"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn plants a sapling of the white tree that blooms before the summer solstice and weds Arwen Undómiel."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["The innkeeper"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Innkeeper who helps Frodo and his companions but is cautious due to their strange behavior","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host (hostility developing)"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Guest (knowledge of each other's true roles under question)"}],"recentEvents":"Handles the upset caused by Frodo's use of the Ring, tries to understand the situation"},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord of Imladris"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Imladris (Rivendell) — Eriador","description":"The Elf-lord and master of Rivendell, who hosted the Fellowship and played a crucial role in their journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host and friend"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and host"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Adviser and ally"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Elrond provides farewell blessings to Frodo, mentions his intention to see Bilbo in the Shire woods around the same time of year."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas","Elladan","Elrohir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lady of Lothlórien.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The daughter of Elrond and mortal woman, Elwing.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"husband"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Marries King Elessar in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Celeborn","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"A dark and foreboding hill range that lies east of the Old Forest, beyond which Tom Bombadil's house is located."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village on the borders of the Shire, known for its inn 'The Prancing Pony'."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The City of the Kings in Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."},{"name":"Hobbiton","description":"The home of hobbits in the Shire, where Frodo and Bilbo live."},{"name":"Shire","description":"The peaceful and hidden region where hobbits live, located in the northwestern part of Middle-earth."}],"summary":"Frodo and his companions prepare to leave Rivendell and the fellowship, while Bilbo offers gifts and advice before his final rest. Gandalf decides to accompany them to Bree, and Frodo plans to return to the Shire to help organize Bilbo’s notes and papers before continuing his journey."}},{"index":69,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["B.B.","Old Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The elderly hobbit who discovered the One Ring and lived in the Shire for a long time.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Bilbo gives Frodo his mithril-coat and Sting, asks Frodo to help tidy and organize his notes and papers, and mentions thinking about joining Gandalf in the woods of the Shire."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin","Gandalf the Gray"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A wizard and advisor to Frodo Baggins and the Fellowship of the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former colleague (now enemy)"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the future of the Shire and left the travelers to return it to peace."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Frodo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The hobbit who bears the One Ring and is the chief protagonist of The Lord of the Rings.","relationships":[{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"servant and loyal companion"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Lord Elrond","relationship":"host"}],"recentEvents":"Stays in Bree and visits Mr. Butterbur. Discussed the current state of the Shire with other travelers."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Merry","Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A young hobbit, friend of Frodo Baggins and an important member of the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"patron and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Speculated about Lotho Sackville-Baggins's involvement in the Shire's troubles."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A gardener's son and loyal friend and servant of Frodo Baggins.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant and loyal companion"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Eowyn","relationship":"mother figure"}],"recentEvents":"Visited his pony Bill in the stable."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion","King Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir to the throne of Gondor, who finally claims his place as king and marries Arwen Undómiel.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"wife"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn plants a sapling of the white tree that blooms before the summer solstice and weds Arwen Undómiel."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butterbur"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"An innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, a popular establishment in Bree.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the current state of the Shire and the travelers' changes since their journey."},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord of Imladris"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Imladris (Rivendell) — Eriador","description":"The Elf-lord and master of Rivendell, who hosted the Fellowship and played a crucial role in their journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host and friend"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and host"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Adviser and ally"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Elrond provides farewell blessings to Frodo, mentions his intention to see Bilbo in the Shire woods around the same time of year."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas","Elladan","Elrohir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lady of Lothlórien.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Departure of Boromir","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"An Istari, now corrupted and plotting against Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman refused to leave Orthanc and will be monitored by Ents."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Flotsam and Jetsam","currentLocation":"Orthanc","description":"A spy and advisor for both Saruman and Théoden that is no longer in power.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Counsellor (formerly)"}],"recentEvents":"Was trapped in Orthanc by Treebeard."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The daughter of Elrond and mortal woman, Elwing.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"husband"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Marries King Elessar in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Celeborn","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo Baggins' hobbit hole in the Shire."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"An area of hills and burial mounds to the south of Bree, where ancient kings were entombed."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village at the crossroads where various travelers meet. It features The Prancing Pony inn, which is the center of local social life."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The City of the Kings in Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."},{"name":"Hobbiton","description":"The home of hobbits in the Shire, where Frodo and Bilbo live."},{"name":"Shire","description":"The land where hobbits live, known for its peace, agricultural productivity, and relative isolation."},{"name":"Brandywine Bridge","description":"A bridge crossing the Brandywine River, marking the entrance to the land of Buckland and the Shire proper."}],"summary":"The four hobbits, Frodo, Merry, Pippin, and Sam, have spent a day in Bree visiting and socializing with locals. Gandalf leaves them, advising them to take care of the Shire themselves. The travelers discuss rumors of unrest and changes in the Shire, but remain hopeful. They prepare to leave for home, but Gandalf warns them of new issues such as gates appearing at the Brandywine Bridge."}},{"index":70,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["B.B.","Old Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The elderly hobbit who discovered the One Ring and lived in the Shire for a long time.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Bilbo gives Frodo his mithril-coat and Sting, asks Frodo to help tidy and organize his notes and papers, and mentions thinking about joining Gandalf in the woods of the Shire."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin","Gandalf the Gray"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A wizard and advisor to Frodo Baggins and the Fellowship of the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"mentor"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"patron"},{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former colleague (now enemy)"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the future of the Shire and left the travelers to return it to peace."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Halfling","Mr. Underhill","Baggins-of-Bag End"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bag End","description":"The primary protagonist of the novel, a hobbit who bears the burden of the One Ring and seeks to destroy it.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Enemy"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and friend"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Servant and close friend"}],"recentEvents":"Confronted and spared Saruman, who then fled Bag End. Witnessed Wormtongue's vengeance on Saruman."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Merry","Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A young hobbit, friend of Frodo Baggins and an important member of the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"patron and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Speculated about Lotho Sackville-Baggins's involvement in the Shire's troubles."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Sammy","Mister Perky"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bag End","description":"Frodo's loyal gardener and best friend who remains steadfast in his support without question.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Servant and trusted friend"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the confrontation with Saruman, killed Wormtongue."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion","King Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir to the throne of Gondor, who finally claims his place as king and marries Arwen Undómiel.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"wife"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn plants a sapling of the white tree that blooms before the summer solstice and weds Arwen Undómiel."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butterbur"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"An innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, a popular establishment in Bree.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the current state of the Shire and the travelers' changes since their journey."},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Lord of Imladris"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Imladris (Rivendell) — Eriador","description":"The Elf-lord and master of Rivendell, who hosted the Fellowship and played a crucial role in their journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Host and friend"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and host"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Adviser and ally"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Friend and ally"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Friend and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Elrond provides farewell blessings to Frodo, mentions his intention to see Bilbo in the Shire woods around the same time of year."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas","Elladan","Elrohir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lady of Lothlórien.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard","Curunir","Sharkey","Curumo"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Bag End","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A corrupted former Maia who became the chief opponent to the Fellowship and sought the power of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant and collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Attacked Frodo but survived, killed by Wormtongue, then vanished."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma","The spy"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Bag End","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Saruman's servant and enforcer, who aided Saruman in his downfall by betraying Rohan and the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant and minion"}],"recentEvents":"Killed Saruman out of hatred and fear."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The daughter of Elrond and mortal woman, Elwing.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"husband"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Marries King Elessar in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Celeborn","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"spouse"}],"recentEvents":"Comes to Minas Tirith for Arwen and Aragorn's wedding."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo's home in the Shire, a cozy and comfortable hobbit hole that has now become a site of confrontation with Saruman."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"An area of hills and burial mounds to the south of Bree, where ancient kings were entombed."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village at the crossroads where various travelers meet. It features The Prancing Pony inn, which is the center of local social life."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The City of the Kings in Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."},{"name":"Hobbiton","description":"The home of hobbits in the Shire, where Frodo and Bilbo live."},{"name":"Shire","description":"The land where hobbits live, known for its peace, agricultural productivity, and relative isolation."},{"name":"Brandywine Bridge","description":"A bridge crossing the Brandywine River, marking the entrance to the land of Buckland and the Shire proper."}],"summary":"Frodo, Sam, and the Shire's hobbits confront Saruman at Bag End. Frodo spares Saruman's life but fails to prevent a final act of betrayal when Wormtongue kills his master and flees, only to be killed himself. Saruman's corrupt remains dissipate in a mist at Bag End, signaling the end of his reign of terror over the Shire."}},{"index":71,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["B.B.","Old Took"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Hobbiton (House of Bilbo) — Shire","description":"The elderly hobbit who discovered the One Ring and lived in the Shire for a long time.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and guide"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Bilbo gives Frodo his mithril-coat and Sting, asks Frodo to help tidy and organize his notes and papers, and mentions thinking about joining Gandalf in the woods of the Shire."},{"name":"Gandalf the Grey","aliases":["The Grey Pilgrim","Gandalf the Grey","Gandalf","the White Rider","Mithrandir","White Wizard","Gandalf the White","Olórin","Olorin","Gandalf the Gray"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Unknown (arrived but not left)","description":"A wizard and leader of the Fellowship, played a significant role in the quest to destroy the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Departed for the West aboard the ship."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Not specified (departed on a ship)","description":"The sole Ring-bearer, who carried the One Ring and completed its destruction.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Uncle"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Friend and former servant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Departed to the Grey Havens and sailed into the West across the Sea."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","aliases":["Lobelia","Mater of the Bagginses"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"A shrewd and somewhat malicious Hobbit with a strong sense of entitlement and a desire for Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"hostile neighbor"},{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"husband"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a conflict with Frodo over Bilbo's possessions and made an unwelcome visit to Bag End."},{"name":"The Hobbits (Merry and Pippin)","aliases":["Merry","Pippin","Master Peregrin","Pippin Took","Peregrin Took","Master Took","Hobbits","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin (Peregrin Took)","Thrice-Great Took","Pippin Peregrin Took","Peregrin","Meriadoc Brandybuck"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Buckland","description":"A hobbit friend of Frodo and Sam, a member of the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Buckland with Merry."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Fellow hobbit and servant of Frodo Baggins, who accompanied Frodo on his journey.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Former master and friend"},{"character":"Rose Cotton","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Stayed behind with Merry and Pippin at the Grey Havens while Frodo, Bilbo, and Gandalf departed."},{"name":"Gildor Inglorion","aliases":["Gildor"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven advisor who encounters Frodo on the road and gives him guidance.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met as a chance encounter with advice"}],"recentEvents":"Gildor provides Frodo with advice regarding his journey and the dangers he faces. He warns him about the threat of the Black Riders and the Enemy but advises haste."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":["Maggot","The Farmer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire who is a friend of Frodo Baggins and has knowledge about the Ring and its whereabouts.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Knows him and speaks to him about the Ring"},{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Informant"}],"recentEvents":"His wisdom about the Ring reaches Tom Bombadil."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown","currentLocation":"Bucklebury","description":"A cousin of Meriadoc Brandybuck and a friend of Frodo.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agrees to stay behind and manage the cover-up in Crickhollow."},{"name":"Old Man Willow","aliases":["None","Tom Bombadil","Old Tom","Bombadillo","none","Éomer","Uglúk","Captain of Gondor","Faramir","Prince of Ithilien","Boromir","Third Marshal of the Mark"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Rider of Rohan and ally of Aragorn","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Led five hundred of his best riders and committed additional foot soldiers to the upcoming campaign."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Nenya"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","currentLocation":"In the House of Tom Bombadil","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she has a connection to water and appears to be knowledgeable and caring.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Entertains Frodo and his companions with a song, assists Tom in welcoming them to their house."},{"name":"Aragorn son of Arathorn","aliases":["Aragorn","Strider","Estel","Elessar","Dúnnadan","Isildur's heir","Elfstone","Thorongil","Herathirion","King Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The heir to the throne of Gondor, who finally claims his place as king and marries Arwen Undómiel.","relationships":[{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"wife"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father-in-law"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn plants a sapling of the white tree that blooms before the summer solstice and weds Arwen Undómiel."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butterbur"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"An innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, a popular establishment in Bree.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed the current state of the Shire and the travelers' changes since their journey."},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Great River","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo’s vanishing act","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Witness"}],"recentEvents":"Reports to Barliman Butterbur about Frodo's disappearance"},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Fellowship of the Ring: The Black Riders","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"A servant at the inn tasked by Mr. Butterbur to help Hobbits.","relationships":[{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Employer or Guide"},{"character":"Mr. Butterbur","relationship":"Employer"}],"recentEvents":"Located the hobbits, helped arrange their bedding and head imitations, and assisted in the watch on the doors."},{"name":"Mister Butterbur","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Prancing Pony","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"The innkeeper of The Prancing Pony, who helps Frodo and company with local information and lodging.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodations and Information Provider"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Sent Nob to help the hobbits and watch for any disturbances around the inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elf-lord"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"An Elf-lord who helps protect Frodo from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Helper and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Glorfindel rode ahead of Frodo on his white horse Asfaloth to ward off the Black Riders and protect Frodo from capture."},{"name":"Black Riders","aliases":["Ringwraiths","Nazgul"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Flight to the Ford","currentLocation":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"Nine dark figures on black horses, they are servants of Sauron seeking the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Pursuers"},{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Nine Black Riders attempted to capture Frodo at the Ford of Bruinen, but were repelled by Glorfindel and overcome by the rising river."},{"name":"Elrond","aliases":["Peredhil","Half-Elf"],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Unknown (departed to the West)","description":"The half-Elf ruler of Rivendell known for his wisdom and his connection to the Valar.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Celebrían","relationship":"Wife (not a direct quote but her spouse)"}],"recentEvents":"Departed for the West aboard the ship."},{"name":"Legolas Greenleaf","aliases":["Legolas","Elladan","Elrohir"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Dawn","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Half-elven son of Elrond, aiding Aragorn in his quest against Sauron","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies with"}],"recentEvents":"Supported Gandalf's strategic counsel against Sauron."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tower of the Stone of Erech","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Dwarf from the Lonely Mountain, loyal and brave.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Fought alongside Legolas, wielding his axe with valor."},{"name":"Balin","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"The Chamber of Mazarbul in Moria","description":"Formerly a member of the Fellowship but died previously in Moria.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Descendant, looks for his kin's tomb"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Former companion"}],"recentEvents":"His tomb was discovered inside Moria."},{"name":"The Balrog","aliases":["Durin's Bane"],"importance":"villain","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Bridge of Khazad-dûm","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shadowy creature of immense power.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Sam","relationship":"Foe"},{"character":"Merry and Pippin","relationship":"Foe"}],"recentEvents":"Engaged in a deadly battle with Gandalf."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fëanorian Art","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elf warrior and guide who leads the travelers within Lothlórien.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Works for and respects the Lady of Lothlórien"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guide and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and describes the power of the land to them."},{"name":"Lady Galadriel","aliases":["Elven-lady","Guardian of Lórien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 6 - Lothlórien","currentLocation":"Lothlórien","description":"An Elven queen of immense power and wisdom, keeper of the Ring Nenya.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"met and tested"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"met"}],"recentEvents":"Galadriel tested Frodo's resolve and offered to take the One Ring, but refused it in favor of continuing her duties to Middle-earth."},{"name":"Galadriel","aliases":["Lady of Lothlórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Fangorn","currentLocation":"Unknown (departed to the West)","description":"A queen of the elven realm of Lothlórien, she possessed the Light of Eärendil and the Mirror of Galadriel.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Celeborn","relationship":"Husband (not a direct quote but her consort)"}],"recentEvents":"Departed for the West aboard the ship."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["The White Wizard","Curunir","Sharkey","Curumo"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Bag End","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A corrupted former Maia who became the chief opponent to the Fellowship and sought the power of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"Servant and collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Attacked Frodo but survived, killed by Wormtongue, then vanished."},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Rider","currentLocation":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A very old and wise Ent, Treebeard is the master of the forest.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard agreed to keep an eye on Saruman trapped in Orthanc."},{"name":"Bregalad","aliases":["Quickbeam"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Ent's Fangs","currentLocation":"Valley of Saruman","description":"A young Ent who was part of the march of the Ents.","relationships":[{"character":"Treebeard","relationship":"Fellow Ent"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the march as one of the Ents going to Isengard."},{"name":"Éomer son of Éomund","aliases":["King of Rohan","Lord of the Mark","Théoden","Théoden King"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Palantír","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King of Rohan, a powerful warrior and leader.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fought valiantly alongside Aragorn, uniting the forces of Rohan and Gondor to defeat Mordor's armies."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Erkenbrand Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Helm's Gate","description":"Lord of Westfold, a warrior and leader of a great part of Rohan's forces. He arrived with reinforcements after the Horn of Helm was blown.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"allies and fellow warriors"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"commander of an army"}],"recentEvents":"Arrived with a thousand men to reinforce Théoden's forces."},{"name":"Wormtongue","aliases":["Gríma","The spy"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Bag End","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Saruman's servant and enforcer, who aided Saruman in his downfall by betraying Rohan and the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant and minion"}],"recentEvents":"Killed Saruman out of hatred and fear."},{"name":"Sméagol","aliases":["Sméagol","Gollum","Slinker","Stinker"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Passage of the Marshes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A treacherous hobbit who was obsessed with the One Ring and ultimately led Frodo to Mount Doom.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accompanied and conflicted over the Ring"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Foe and competitor for the Ring"}],"recentEvents":"Gollum falls to his death into a fiery abyss, resulting in the destruction of the One Ring."},{"name":"Gollum/Sméagol","aliases":["the creeping Sméagol"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the World","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"A creature of ambiguous moral standing, formerly known as Sméagol, who guides Frodo with a mix of malevolent intention and dependency on the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and reluctant companion"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"Detected by Faramir as having committed murder and possessing malice"}],"recentEvents":"Guides Frodo across dangerous and ominous Ithilien; warned against cirith Ungol by Faramir."},{"name":"Shelob","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"A giant spider who lurks in the tunnels seeking prey.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"She was mentioned but not physically encountered."},{"name":"Shagrat","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Gorbag","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Captures Frodo and takes him to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Gorbag","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Prisoner in Barad-dûr","currentLocation":"Barad-dûr","description":"An Orc guard who interacts with Frodo and Sam.","relationships":[{"character":"Shagrat","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Joins Shagrat in taking Frodo to Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Beregond","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"A soldier of Gondor defending Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Fought in the battle, was knocked over by a troll but was saved by Pippin."},{"name":"Bergil","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of Beregond, Bergil is a young boy who enjoys spending time with Pippin.","relationships":[{"character":"Beregond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Fondness and friendship"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Pippin around the city, showed him his father as well as his greetings and hopes for the future."},{"name":"Forlong the Fat","aliases":[""],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Window on the West","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lossarnach and one of the leaders of troops marching to Minas Tirith","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Led his men to Minas Tirith with heavy hearts knowing he didn't bring as many as expected."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince Imrahil"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Morannon","description":"Prince of Dol Amroth and an ally to Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the battle against Mordor's forces, commanding men from Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Dernhelm","Éowyn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of The King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A noblewoman and warrior of Rohan, deeply affected by the war.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"friend and ally"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"loved and devoted to him"}],"recentEvents":"Éowyn is recovering in the Houses of Healing, wishing to leave soon but restrained by Aragorn's recommendation to stay until at least ten days have passed."},{"name":"Denethor","aliases":["Lord of Minas Tirith","Steward"],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The last Ruling Steward of Gondor, consumed by despair and madness.","relationships":[{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"son, deceased"},{"character":"Faramir","relationship":"son"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Committed suicide by burning himself in the Houses of the Dead, leading to chaos."},{"name":"Guthláf","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell fighting the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Wídfara","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Minas Tirith Attack","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith outskirts","description":"A rider from Rohan predicting the change in circumstances.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Provided a weather forecast predicting an upcoming dawn."},{"name":"Forlong son of Borastir","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Captain of the Morthond Vale.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the forces of Mordor."},{"name":"Duilin of Morthond","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Hirluin the Fair","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The son of the Lord of Pinnath Gelin, a captain of the men of Pinnath Gelin.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle against the foes of Gondor."},{"name":"Grimbold","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell in the battle against the orcs."},{"name":"Halbarad","aliases":["Rangers of the North"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A Ranger from the North, an ally to Aragorn and a tracker.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"comrade"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"comrade"}],"recentEvents":"Led Dúnedain troops from the North to fight in the battle."},{"name":"Forlong's brother","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"A soldier in Gondor's military.","relationships":[{"character":"Forlong son of Borastir","relationship":"brother"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"ally"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"ally"}],"recentEvents":"Fell alongside his brother while fighting the mûmakil."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["The Dark Lord","The Enemy"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Morannon","currentLocation":"Mordor","description":"The evil ruler of Mordor who seeks to conquer Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"enemy"},{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"former ally, now enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Initiated a massive assault on the forces of the West after his terms were rejected."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The White Tree","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The daughter of Elrond and mortal woman, Elwing.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"husband"},{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"father"}],"recentEvents":"Marries King Elessar in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Celeborn","aliases":["Lord of Lothlórien"],"importance":"secondary","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Unknown (departed to the West)","description":"A noble elf lord of Lothlórien, husband to Galadriel.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Departed for the West aboard the ship."},{"name":"Rose Cotton","aliases":["Rose Gardner"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"The wife of Samwise Gamgee, Rose was a resident of the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Wife"},{"character":"Elanor Gamgee","relationship":"Daughter"}],"recentEvents":"Received Samwise back at Bywater."},{"name":"Elanor Gamgee","aliases":["Lanor"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"The young daughter of Samwise and Rose Gamgee.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Rose Gamgee","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received Samwise back at Bywater."}],"locations":[{"name":"Bag End","description":"Frodo's home in the Shire, a cozy and comfortable hobbit hole that has now become a site of confrontation with Saruman."},{"name":"Bywater","description":"A town in the Shire located near Bywater Hill, often a point of contention for disputes among Hobbits."},{"name":"The Ferry","description":"A crossing point in the Shire where the travelers need to go to safely continue their journey."},{"name":"Old Forest","description":"An enchanting yet perilous forest that houses ancient trees like Old Man Willow who possess a malevolent nature."},{"name":"Bucklebury","description":"The settlement in Buckland where Frodo and his friends plan and partially prepare for a covert departure."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","description":"A cozy and inviting home where Tom Bombadil resides, located beyond the borders of the Old Forest and the edge of the Barrow-downs."},{"name":"Barrow-downs","description":"An area of hills and burial mounds to the south of Bree, where ancient kings were entombed."},{"name":"House of Tom Bombadil","description":"A humble house in the edge of the Old Forest, known for its warmth and comfort, visited by Frodo and his companions."},{"name":"Bree","description":"A small village at the crossroads where various travelers meet. It features The Prancing Pony inn, which is the center of local social life."},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Inn located in Bree, a place where different peoples from all over the Shire and the surrounding regions gather to socialize and trade"},{"name":"Weathertop","description":"A high hill where the Hobbits and Strider seek shelter, but it becomes a site of danger when shadowy figures appear."},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","description":"A river crossing where the River Bruinen intersects the path from Bree to Rivendell."},{"name":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Last Homely House and refuge in the Ered Luin (Blue Mountains). It is a haven for weary travelers and Elves of great skill and lore."},{"name":"Hall of Fire","description":"A chamber in Rivendell where Elves gather to sing, tell tales, and listen to poetry during evening merrymaking."},{"name":"Rivendell","description":"An ancient Elven stronghold where Elrond resides, providing a haven for those in need."},{"name":"Misty Mountains","description":"A mountain range that defines the eastern edge of the Shire and separates Eriador from Wilderland."},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","description":"A perilous pass through the Misty Mountains where a heavy snowstorm forced the Fellowship to endure."},{"name":"Moria","description":"An ancient Dwarven city and massive underground realm with its own Great Gates and Dimrill Dale."},{"name":"Khazad-dûm","description":"The ancient Dwarf-mine that has since been inhabited by orcs and is home to the Balrog."},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","description":"A vale at the east foot of the Misty Mountains, near the Gates of Moria."},{"name":"Lothlórien","description":"A forested region in Middle-earth ruled by Lady Galadriel, the guardian of the Ring Nenya."},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A hill in Lothlórien, famous as the site of Amroth's high house and home to the 'Lady of the Galadhrim'."},{"name":"Southern Mirkwood","description":"A dark, firtree-covered forest opposite Lothlórien, with a hidden fortress of Dol Guldur within."},{"name":"Anduin River","description":"A great river running southward from Lórien, part of the journey as the Fellowship moves closer to Mordor."},{"name":"Lórien","description":"An enchanted forest realm of the elves beneath a silver light, now departed from by the Fellowship."},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","description":"A lake in the middle of the River Anduin, enclosed by Emyn Muil hills and featuring the three hills of Amon Hen, Amon Lhaw, and Tol Brandir."},{"name":"Emyn Muil","description":"An area of steep hills and cliffs located east of the inland sea of Nen Hithoel, where Frodo and Sam are held captive by Gollum."},{"name":"Argonath","description":"The Pillars of the Kings, towering stone statues on either side of the River Anduin marking the passage through the Emyn Muil."},{"name":"Tol Brandir","description":"A tall, isolated peak in the middle of Nen Hithoel, said to be unscalable by any man."},{"name":"Amon Hen","description":"A hill with a watchtower overlooking the Anduin River, where Boromir meets his fate."},{"name":"Amon Lhaw","description":"An island in the Anduin river, where Frodo and Sam land after their departure from the others."},{"name":"Parth Galen","description":"A green lawn beside the Anduin River opposite Minas Tirith, where the Fellowship breaks."},{"name":"Rauros-falls","description":"A location near Parth Galen with waterfalls where Aragorn imagines Frodo and his belongings have been carried."},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A vast and ancient forest that borders the eastern side of the Entwash River, known for its towering trees and dense undergrowth."},{"name":"Entwash","description":"A marshy river in Rohan, fed by several streams which merge to form a large fen"},{"name":"Valley of Saruman","description":"The valley where Saruman's stronghold, Orthanc, lies surrounded by Isengard."},{"name":"Eastemnet, Rohan","description":"A vast open plain in Rohan, used for grazing horses and other livestock, where Gandalf and his companions travel."},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","description":"A low mountain pass near the borders of Rohan, currently displaying a large smoke cloud indicating ongoing conflict and war."},{"name":"Helm's Gate","description":"A large fortress guarding the northern entrance to Rohan, protected by natural defenses and the Horn of Helm."},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","description":"A valley surrounded by hills and cliffs, where the forces of Isengard were trapped and defeated."},{"name":"Isengard","description":"A fortress of the White Council located in the valley of the rivers Isen and Entwash, now under control of the Ents."},{"name":"Isen","description":"A fortress built by Saruman for industry and military purposes that has been destroyed by Ents."},{"name":"Fangorn's Wood","description":"A large forested area near Isengard where Ents dwell."},{"name":"The Watchwood","description":"A new designation for the area around Isengard where Ents will watch over Saruman."},{"name":"Minas Tirith","description":"The City of the Kings in Gondor."},{"name":"Orthanc","description":"An immense black tower, the ancient keep of Isengard and the stronghold of Saruman."},{"name":"Edoras","description":"The hill-city and capital of Rohan, home to the kings of the Mark"},{"name":"Mordor","description":"A dark and ominous region controlled by Sauron with dangerous terrain and creatures guarding his lands."},{"name":"Morannon","description":"The Black Gate of Mordor, site of the final battle between Sauron's forces and those of the West."},{"name":"Ithilien","description":"The easternmost part of Gondor, once beautiful but now haunting since under the control of Minas Morgul. Faramir's territory, filled with fear and lurking dangers."},{"name":"Cave in Ithilien","description":"A secret cave in the wildlands of Ithilien, used by R Rangers and perhaps others who seek refuge from open ground."},{"name":"Minas Ithil","description":"A former Gondorian city, now called Minas Morgul and a place of decay, malice, and darkness."},{"name":"Cirith Ungol","description":"A jagged pass high in Mordor's mountains, guarded by the Tower."},{"name":"Cross-roads","description":"A significant junction in the landscape near the foot of the mountains, where ancient trees form a roofless ring around a central point."},{"name":"Osgiliath","description":"Ruined city and now a strategic bridgehead between Gondor and Mordor."},{"name":"Tunnel complex under Barad-dûr","description":"Underground network including chambers and a large gate."},{"name":"Erech","description":"A hill where Isildur set a black stone, known as the Stone of Erech, as a trysting-place for the Shadow-men."},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A valley that lies beside the River Morthond, which eventually flows to the sea near Dol Amroth."},{"name":"Calembel","description":"A township found deserted, with men having escaped to the hills upon hearing the Grey Company's approach."},{"name":"Dunharrow","description":"A strong hold in the mountains of Rohan where Men hid from foes in times of great fear"},{"name":"Snowbourn","description":"A river in Rohan which flows through hamlets of Underharrow and Upbourn, north of Edoras"},{"name":"Halifirien","description":"A mountain by the borders of Rohan, part of a line of beacon hills that are quenched in darkness"},{"name":"Silent Street","description":"Location within Minas Tirith where Denethor and Faramir are taken."},{"name":"Rath Dínen","description":"The sacred place of the tombs of the Stewards of Gondor where Denethor committed suicide."},{"name":"Houses of Healing","description":"Medical facility within Minas Tirith, currently treating the wounded."},{"name":"Lossarnach","description":"A fiefdom in South Gondor contributing troops to the war effort."},{"name":"Pelargir","description":"Port city south of Osgiliath, a staging area for forces against Mordor."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in Mordor, steeped in fear and filled with fallen orcs."},{"name":"Udûn","description":"A region of Mordor with high walls and dark roads leading into Barad-dûr."},{"name":"Mount Doom","description":"A volcanic mountain in Mordor, where the One Ring was forged and must be destroyed to end the Dark Lord Sauron's control."},{"name":"Hobbiton","description":"The home of hobbits in the Shire, where Frodo and Bilbo live."},{"name":"Shire","description":"The land where hobbits live, known for its peace, agricultural productivity, and relative isolation."},{"name":"Brandywine Bridge","description":"A bridge crossing the Brandywine River, marking the entrance to the land of Buckland and the Shire proper."},{"name":"The Grey Havens","description":"The port city where the Elves depart for their ultimate destination beyond the sea."},{"name":"Mithlond","description":"An alternative name for the Grey Havens, the port city where the elves prepare to depart."}],"summary":"Frodo, Bilbo, Gandalf, and other elves leave Middle-earth to sail into the West across the Sea, while Sam, Merry, and Pippin remain in the Shire to continue their lives there."}}],"bookMeta":{"chapters":[{"id":"title-1","title":"Title Page","order":0,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"epig-1","title":"Part 2","order":1,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"toc","title":"Table of Contents","order":2,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"pref-1","title":"NOTE ON THE TEXT","order":3,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"intr-1","title":"NOTE ON THE 50TH ANNIVERSARY EDITION","order":4,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"fore-1","title":"FOREWORD TO THE SECOND EDITION","order":5,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"prol-1","title":"PROLOGUE","order":6,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"part-0","title":"THE FELLOWSHIP OF THE RING","order":7,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"chap-1","title":"Chapter 1: A LONG-EXPECTED PARTY","order":8,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"chap-2","title":"Chapter 2: THE SHADOW OF THE PAST","order":9,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"chap-3","title":"Chapter 3: THREE IS COMPANY","order":10,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"chap-4","title":"Chapter 4: A SHORT CUT TO MUSHROOMS","order":11,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"chap-5","title":"Chapter 5: A CONSPIRACY UNMASKED","order":12,"bookIndex":0,"book